# Google API Keys for Weather Integration
# Get these from Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/

# Google Maps API Key (for geocoding location data)
# Required scopes: Geocoding API
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here

# Weather API Key (using OpenWeatherMap as proxy for Google Weather)
# Get from: https://openweathermap.org/api
OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=your_openweathermap_api_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
# 3. VITE_ prefixed keys are for client-side use
# 4. Non-prefixed keys are for server-side Netlify Functions
# 5. Configure domain restrictions in Google Cloud Console for security
# 6. Never commit .env.local to version control

# For Netlify deployment:
# Set these environment variables in your Netlify dashboard under Site Settings > Environment Variables